@junrao My last commit remove the code that explicitly sets the default tags, and instead use `metrics.metricName(name, group, description)` to create `MetricName` with default tags.

I still kept the explicit usage of `metricTags` in `Selector` because `ControllerChannelManager.addNewBroker(Broker)` needs the flexibility to changes tags.

Could you have a look and let me know if this is what you originally suggested? Thanks!

@granders

> To clarify, do you mean that minikdc is broken in general by these changes? 

Not really, it is just the way it is set up in `kafka.py` that makes it a bit hard to get it to work with this test case without shuffling some code unrelated to the test. It seems very possible to do it, but I wanted to have a working test before making other changes. In fact, my suggestion is that we do a test case separately enabling kerberos with ZK. For now, we just need a test case that show that the rolling upgrade with ZK works.
